ce:section.ce:para:
On the basis of the above results, we proposed that the enhanced photocatalytic activity under visible light irradiation could be attributed to the synergistic effect of C-doping and PPDs hybridization (Scheme 2
                        ). Under visible light irradiation, the absorbed light energy may cause photoexcited electrons transfer. In the transferring process of e− in CB of C-hTiO2 to PPDs, O2 could react with the e− to generate O2

                           −, which then attacked ABTS. Simultaneously, the photogenerated h+ as a result of e− transition on the VB of C-hTiO2 could react with H2O to form OH for the oxidation of ABTS. Overall, in the photocatalytic process, the C-doping can synergistically enhance the light absorption and/or facilitate the electron transfer in PPDs/C-hTiO2.
